<div class="cd-container cd-section">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">

    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl">Accessibility Statement</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">This statement applies to <strong>{{ business.seo.site_url }}</strong>. Last reviewed: {{ (business.legal.accessibility_reviewed | readableDate) if (business.legal and business.legal.accessibility_reviewed) else ("now" | currentYear) }}. We review this statement annually and after any major site changes.</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-10 text-[var(--color-body-text)]">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl text-white">Our commitment</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">{{ business.business_name }} is committed to ensuring this website is accessible to the widest possible audience, including people with disabilities. We aim to conform to the <strong>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2 at Level AA</strong>.</p>
        <p class="mt-3">We actively work to make our websites usable by people who rely on keyboard navigation, screen readers, high-contrast modes, or other assistive technologies.</p>
        <p class="mt-3">Under the Equality Act 2010, we have a duty to make reasonable adjustments so that disabled people are not disadvantaged when using our website.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl text-white">Conformance status</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">This website is <strong>partially conformant</strong> with WCAG 2.2 Level AA. Partially conformant means that some parts of the content do not fully conform to the accessibility standard.</p>
        <p class="mt-3">Key accessibility features this site includes:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
          <li>Skip-to-content link at the top of every page for keyboard users.</li>
          <li>All interactive elements are keyboard-navigable with a visible focus indicator.</li>
          <li>Focused elements are not obscured by the sticky navigation bar (WCAG 2.4.11).</li>
          <li>Colour contrast ratios meet WCAG AA minimums: ≥4.5:1 for normal text, ≥3:1 for large text and UI components.</li>
          <li>All form inputs have associated labels (visible or screen-reader accessible).</li>
          <li>Images include descriptive <code>alt</code> text, or empty <code>alt=""</code> where decorative.</li>
          <li>Semantic HTML headings (<code>h1</code>-<code>h3</code>) are used in a logical order.</li>
          <li>Page language is declared (<code>lang="{{ business.seo.locale }}"</code>).</li>
          <li>Interactive elements meet minimum touch target sizes (WCAG 2.5.8).</li>
          <li>Animations and transitions are suppressed when the user has requested reduced motion.</li>
          <li>Page structure uses semantic landmark elements (<code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;main&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code>).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl text-white">Known limitations</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">We are aware of the following areas that may not fully meet WCAG 2.2 AA:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
          <li><strong>Third-party embeds</strong> - booking widgets, maps, or video embeds from external providers may not fully conform. We encourage providers to meet accessibility standards but cannot guarantee them.</li>
          <li><strong>PDF documents</strong> - any linked PDF files may not be fully accessible. Please contact us if you need the content in an alternative format.</li>
          <li><strong>Older blog content</strong> - historical blog posts may predate our current accessibility standards. We aim to update these over time.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl text-white">Technical information</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">{{ business.business_name }} relies on the following technologies for WCAG 2.2 conformance:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
          <li>HTML5</li>
          <li>CSS (including ARIA roles and landmark regions)</li>
          <li>JavaScript (for interactive components such as navigation menus, carousels, and accordions)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl text-white">Feedback and contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">We welcome feedback on the accessibility of this website. If you experience any barriers or difficulty accessing content, please let us know:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a class="text-[var(--color-accent-link)] hover:underline" href="mailto:{{ business.contact.email }}">{{ business.contact.email }}</a></li>
          <li><strong>Phone:</strong> <a class="text-[var(--color-accent-link)] hover:underline" href="{{ business.contact.phone_href }}">{{ business.contact.phone }}</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within 5 business days and to resolve issues, or provide an alternative, within 30 days.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl text-white">Formal complaints procedure</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">If you are not satisfied with our response, or if you need to escalate a complaint, you can contact the <strong>Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC)</strong>:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm">
          <li>Website: <a class="text-[var(--color-accent-link)] hover:underline" href="https://www.equalityhumanrights.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">equalityhumanrights.com</a></li>
          <li>Helpline: 0808 800 0082</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">In Scotland, contact <a class="text-[var(--color-accent-link)] hover:underline" href="https://www.equalityhumanrights.com/about-us/our-offices/scotland-office" target="_blank" rel="noopener">EHRC Scotland</a>.</p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>
